 EVALUATION PROCEDURE                                             9131 1451
                                                                  9131 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                9131 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               9131 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             9131 1451
                                                                  9131 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              9131 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b33 by                    9131 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               9131 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               9131 1451
 and features, relevant for this evaluation:                      9131 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 9131 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         9131 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    9131 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              9131 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      9131 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 9131 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                9131 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   9131 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                9131 1451
   discrete transitions                                           9131 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              9131 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                9131 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               9131 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              9131 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 9131 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              9131 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           9131 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    9131 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 9131 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                9131 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      9131 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        9131 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               9131 1451
